name: Scott Huebner
bio: Husband, Veteran, Colorado. Hybrid Burl  Alpine Artwork, place a piece of the mountains 🏔in your hands or home. Available at hunterwolffgallery.com

social_posts.post_text:
New 6” double cap maple burl.  Casted in light blue with a little galaxy mix.  Perfect for being placed on a lighted rotating stand.
#resin #epoxy #woodandresin #woodturning
4” Maple burl, casted in Amber.  This piece was casted with @resin_pro resin.  They were kind enough to send me their resin to try out.  Very nice product, thank you.  I will be using it again.
4” stained maple burl, casted in lemon yellow.  Headed off to the gallery.
Finally back in the shop again.  About to start polishing this 6” Amazon burl, casted in copper.  #resinart #resinandwood #woodturning

6” Massaranduba Amazonian burl casted in copper resin.  With my wife currently stable, in her battle against cancer.  I am finally able to get back into the shop.  This piece has been waiting a while, to be completed.  Hope you like it.  Thanks for all your support and prayers.  #woodturning #resinart #woodandresin
New copper and ambrosia maple charcuterie board in progress.
Beveled Ambrosia Maple, with a bit of spalting, and copper resin. Brushed brass handles and rubber feet.  #woodworking #charcuterieboard #resinandwood #resinart
The glow has been added and ready for casting.
Completed 6” color shifting Maple burl cap, casted in sky blue.  With glowing snow fields. #resinart #woodandresin #woodworking #woodturning #epoxyart
Working on a new 4” Maple
Slow motion pour, crystal clear.

Puppy Patrol, highlights reel.
#gsd #longcoatgsd #germanshepherd #longcoatgermanshepherd #germanshepherd.owners

4” color shifting Maple burl cap.  Casted in clear, with glowing snow fields. 

#resinart #epoxy #epoxyandwood #woodturning #letsresin
Some still shots of the new 4” (Edilewise) Maple piece.

Merlot and Ambrosia Maple Charcuterie board.  With rubber feet and brushed brass handles.
 

#charcuterieboard #woodandresin #epoxy #woodworking
Applying the glowing snow fields, on a new 4” piece.

Butcher block charcuterie board, with rubber feet and brushed brass handles.
#charcuterieboard #woodworking #handmade

4” color shifting Maple burl cap, casted in purple.  I made this one a little darker, so that it can sit in direct sunlight, that will make it really pop.  Unfortunately it is overcast today and not able to show the full effect.
I love how crystal clear the blanks are, with a new mold. 🤙🏼 working on a new 6”

Wonderful pictures of the Merlot and Ambrosia Maple Charcuterie board.  Provided by Sharon @hunterwolffgallery , where the board is available.  Please visit the gallery and all of the talented artists that they represent.  Thank you 🙏🏼
Finished sanding and about to start polishing.  #woodturning #woodworking #epoxy #woodandresin #resinart
Completed (Wildfire). 6” natural cap maple burl, casted in flame red.  #woodworking #woodturning #epoxy #resinart #resinandwood #hybridart
Finally able to get back into the shop.  It’s been a hectic summer.  New 4” piece casted, Ruby red on Red Mallee.  This will be turned this weekend.
Completed 4” Red Mallee, casted in Ruby red.  #resinart #woodandresin #woodturning #allumilite

Bronze, spalted ambrosia maple Charcuterie board.  Heading out to Seattle tomorrow.
